jobs_results.description:
Create cutting-edge mobile apps that have a profound impact on people's lives worldwide.
Job Title

iOS Developer
About the Role

We're seeking an innovative and detail-oriented iOS developer to join our team of ideas and results engineers.

As an iOS developer, you will be responsible for creating new projects from scratch, delivering new features, and reacting to customer feedback and internal user testing.
Your Responsibilities
• Develop high-quality iOS applications for areas such as augmented reality, healthcare, and retailing.
• Work closely with our design and content teams to deliver exceptional user experiences.
• Maintain a deep understanding of the latest iOS development trends and best practices.
Requirements

To succeed in this role, you'll need:
• At least 2 years of experience in iOS development (Obj-C and/or Swift).
• A degree in Informatics and Computing Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field.
• The ability to manage entire app development life-cycle.
What We Offer

As a member of our team, you can expect:
• A competitive salary of $90,000 - $110,000 per year, depending on your level of experience.

jobs_results.title: Mobile developer (Android ou iOS)
iOS Mobile Developer for Sports Entertainment Solutions
jobs_results.description:
Job Overview
At Devoteam Portugal, we are looking to hire an experienced iOS Developer who can contribute to the development of our innovative mobile solutions in the sports entertainment sector.

About You
We are seeking a skilled and motivated individual with at least 4 years of experience in mobile development using Swift. Strong knowledge and expertise in RESTful APIs, MVP and MVVM architectures, multi-threading, and asynchronous logic are essential for this role.

Responsibilities
As an iOS Developer, you will work closely with cross-functional teams to design, develop, and implement high-quality mobile applications that meet our customers' expectations. Your primary focus will be on delivering technically sound solutions that adhere to industry standards and best practices.

Qualifications
To succeed in this position, you should have:
• A minimum of 4 years of experience in iOS development using Swift
• Strong knowledge of RESTful APIs
• Experience with MVP and MVVM architectures
• Expertise in multi-threading and asynchronous logic
• Familiarity with agile development methodologies and Scrum

Preferred Qualifications
Nice to have: knowledge of Cocoa Touch, Firebase, MapBox, Clean Architecture, and MVI. Experience with Git Flow, Jira, and Confluence is also a plus.

About Our Company
Devoteam Group is committed to promoting equal opportunities and diversity within our organization. We believe that diversity contributes to creativity, dynamism, and excellence. All our vacancies are open to people with disabilities. The estimated salary for this position is €60,000 - €80,000 per year, depending on your experience and qualifications.

jobs_results.title: Lead iOS Developer for Pain-Free Healthcare Solutions
jobs_results.description:
Sword Health is revolutionizing the healthcare industry by harnessing technology to predict, prevent, and treat pain. As a Senior iOS Engineer, you will play a pivotal role in designing and building software applications that empower users to take control of their health.

Company Overview

Sword Health is a pioneering company that has gained recognition as a Forbes Best Startup Employer in 2023. Our mission is to create a pain-free world, powered by technology and enhanced by people. With a recent valuation of $2 billion, we are experiencing hyper growth and expansion, and we're seeking talented individuals like you to join our team.

Salary and Benefits

We offer a competitive salary range of EUR 40,000 - 60,000, along with a comprehensive benefits package that includes flexible working hours, unlimited vacation, and access to our health and well-being program (digital therapist sessions). Additionally, you'll have the opportunity to work remotely or hybrid in Portugal, making it an ideal location for those seeking a balance between work and personal life.

Job Description

As a Lead iOS Developer, your key responsibilities will include:
• Designing and building high-performance software applications for iOS
• Ensuring the quality and responsiveness of applications
• Participating in projects that drive innovation and growth
• Troubleshooting and debugging to optimize performance
• Collaborating with cross-functional teams to deliver exceptional results

Required Skills and Qualifications

To excel in this role, you'll need:
• More than 4 years of experience in developing and shipping iOS Applications
• Proficiency in iOS, Swift, and relevant frameworks
• Experience with cloud message APIs and push notifications
• Familiarity with code versioning tools and agile development methodologies

Why Choose Sword Health?

We're not just looking for developers – we're looking for passionate individuals who share our vision of creating a pain-free world. Join our dynamic team and be part of something revolutionary. Apply now to become a part of our journey towards shaping the future of healthcare.

jobs_results.title: Ofera de emprego: Emprego: iOS Mobile Developer
Senior Mobile Software Engineer - Swift and Cocoa Touch
jobs_results.description:
About Us
Mindera is a software engineering company that uses technology to build products we are proud of, with people we love.
We partner with our clients to understand their products and deliver high-performance, resilient and scalable software systems that create an impact in their users and businesses across the world.

Job Summary
We are seeking an experienced Senior Mobile Software Engineer to join our team. As a Senior Mobile Software Engineer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining high-quality mobile applications using Swift and Cocoa Touch. You will work collaboratively with our cross-functional team to ensure that our applications meet the highest standards of quality, performance, and reliability.

Responsibilities
- Design, develop, and maintain high-quality mobile applications using Swift and Cocoa Touch
- Collaborate with our cross-functional team to ensure that our applications meet the highest standards of quality, performance, and reliability
- Develop and maintain automated tests to ensure the stability and reliability of our applications
- Participate in code reviews to ensure that our codebase remains clean and well-organized
- Stay up-to-date with the latest technologies and trends in mobile development
- Work collaboratively with our QA team to identify and resolve issues in our applications

Requirements
- 5+ years of experience in mobile software development
- Proficiency in Swift and Cocoa Touch
- Experience with Agile development methodologies and Scrum framework
- Strong understanding of software design patterns and architecture
- Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail
- Ability to communicate effectively with team members and stakeholders

Benefits
- Competitive salary: €80,000 - €100,000 per year
- Health insurance
- Flexible working hours
- Open holidays and time off for personal activities
- Profit distribution for everyone
- Mindera Annual Trip and sports groups to connect and have fun
- Training & conferences, create your own training plan
- Child Care vouchers
- Hotspot with unlimited usage for work or personal use

Company Culture
We are a politics-free environment where the whole team owns the project together. We encourage our colleagues to take risks, make decisions, work in a collaborative way, and talk to everyone to enhance communication. Freedom and responsibility go hand-in-hand, and we value commitment, feedback, and empathy.

jobs_results.title: Senior Mobile Developer (RN, iOS, Android)
jobs_results.description: Since 2015 Sweatcoin and now Sweat Economy is working on making the world more physically active. With more than 100 million registered users, thousands of partners and a proven ability to make people move more (+20%) Sweat Economy has already become the largest onramp in web3 history. We now working on turning our token - $SWEAT - into the principal unit of physical activity value and building an economy of movement around it. As a Senior Mobile Developer, you will contribute the team for making the Sweat Wallet app into the best multichain mobile wallet on the market with tens of millions of users. You will work on : The tasks are complex and exciting - cosmic UI, optimization of battery consumption, GPS / Motion, Anti-fraud and Security, analytics and growth & A/B testing. Most of the UI is implemented with React Native. The overall stack is Android/iOS SDK + Kotlin + Swift + React Native. Work day-to-day in a multinational cross-functional team of engineers, designers, and product managers to build the best fitness & health app Collaborate with other service teams on evolving our shared processes and tooling to support a large number of teams working on a diverse array of products Explore new ways of solving cross-platform design problems at scale Apply, if You have: Portfolio of consumer-facing high-performance mobile applications available in stores Advanced React Native skills Android SDK / Kotlin / Apple iOS SDK / Swift would be an advantage Good understanding of sensors, Google-play, Apple services Be able to write maintainable and readable code, good knowledge of design patterns Self-motivated and able to achieve deadlines and work independently English - Upper-Intermediate or above You care deeply about usability, accessibility and performance You are eager to learn new technologies (we will support you with training & mentoring) We value and pay attention to self-education and self-improvement in all areas, even not related to the profession, that is of interest to you. What you get in return: Remote-friendly & Flexible working hours. The flexibility is incredible, performance is based on output, rather than hours spent working, you can be wherever you want! Apple devices for work Team buildings abroad in exciting locations, when borders are open, we will announce the next adventure! Health insurance coverage WellBeing program, which supports up to 2 counselling sessions per month Unlimited time-off policy If you feel that's a match we would be excited to have you on our team!
